method of a string,
he says, this is

00:18:53.757 --> 00:18:54.855
the method of a string.

00:18:54.855 --> 00:19:00.946
And he'll label an equation with
the whole, writes it out.

00:19:00.946 --> 00:19:02.180
In [INAUDIBLE] terms.

00:19:02.180 --> 00:19:02.460
PROFESSOR: Right.

00:19:02.460 --> 00:19:03.720
He'll write everything out.

00:19:03.720 --> 00:19:05.600
So he's very explicit
about notation.

00:19:05.600 --> 00:19:06.850
How does that help
the students?

00:19:10.474 --> 00:19:11.610
What does that do for them?

00:19:11.610 --> 00:19:11.966
Yes.

00:19:11.966 --> 00:19:14.552
AUDIENCE: It makes it
clearer and it makes

00:19:14.552 --> 00:19:16.740
mistakes hard to make.

00:19:16.740 --> 00:19:16.970
PROFESSOR: Right.

00:19:16.970 --> 00:19:19.010
It makes it hard to
make mistakes.

00:19:19.010 --> 00:19:24.534
Again, so this is hard
to make mistakes.

00:19:24.534 --> 00:19:25.784
Harder--

00:19:32.230 --> 00:19:32.570
OK.

00:19:32.570 --> 00:19:36.950
And what makes it harder, and
why is this so important?

00:19:36.950 --> 00:19:40.550
Because, as Adrian said, yeah,
it may be intuitively obvious

00:19:40.550 --> 00:19:42.990
to the expert physicist that,
of course, L is the length.

00:19:42.990 --> 00:19:46.230
That's why you chose L, because
length begins with L.

00:19:46.230 --> 00:19:50.090
But for the student,
everything is new.

00:19:50.090 --> 00:19:52.860
The chess example, the knocking
down the chessboard

00:19:52.860 --> 00:19:55.490
problem and seeing how well
you can reconstruct it,

00:19:55.490 --> 00:19:57.860
explains so much.

00:19:57.860 --> 00:20:00.480
The novice, they can't
reconstruct the chessboard.

00:20:00.480 --> 00:20:03.140
That's because each piece
on the chessboard is not

00:20:03.140 --> 00:20:04.480
intuitively obvious.

00:20:04.480 --> 00:20:06.650
Whereas, for the chess master,
it's so easy to reconstruct

00:20:06.650 --> 00:20:09.170
the board, because, to them,
it is intuitively obvious

00:20:09.170 --> 00:20:10.735
that, of course, you
have three pawns in

00:20:10.735 --> 00:20:11.680
front of your king.

00:20:11.680 --> 00:20:14.100
Unless you have some really
crazy opening, of course

00:20:14.100 --> 00:20:15.990
you've castled your kind and you
have three pawns sitting

00:20:15.990 --> 00:20:18.136
in front of it protecting it.

00:20:18.136 --> 00:20:21.890
And it's just obvious from the
configuration of the pawns

00:20:21.890 --> 00:20:24.080
that, of course, with that pawn
configuration you did

00:20:24.080 --> 00:20:24.670
this opening.

00:20:24.670 --> 00:20:27.620
And of course, the king is
defended in this way.

00:20:27.620 --> 00:20:31.610
So what's obvious to the expert
is completely obscure

00:20:31.610 --> 00:20:32.860
to the non-expert.

00:20:35.446 --> 00:20:39.090
You want them to not have to
worry and fill up their

00:20:39.090 --> 00:20:41.500
short-term memory slots with
things that really are

00:20:41.500 --> 00:20:44.380
obvious, so you put that
right on the diagram.

00:20:46.980 --> 00:20:49.240
He wrote M, I think, and then
there was an L there.

00:20:49.240 --> 00:20:51.120
So right away, you just
look at the diagram.

00:20:51.120 --> 00:20:54.540
You know what L is.

00:20:54.540 --> 00:20:55.040
OK.

00:20:55.040 --> 00:20:57.030
Other things that were done?

00:20:57.030 --> 00:20:58.280
There are so many.

