01:09:16.600 --> 01:09:18.574
I think what I would do is I
would show them that goals--

01:09:21.600 --> 01:09:24.660
Goals are OK, as long as you
don't begin the lecture by

01:09:24.660 --> 01:09:27.880
saying, here are my goals,
because that's that secret

01:09:27.880 --> 01:09:29.109
time you're taking away from.

01:09:29.109 --> 01:09:31.880
I would put the goals, say, on
a side board, so they can see

01:09:31.880 --> 01:09:34.460
them all the time, or write the,
just after you've done

01:09:34.460 --> 01:09:35.729
your punchline.

01:09:35.729 --> 01:09:36.779
Then put them all up.

01:09:36.779 --> 01:09:38.710
AUDIENCE: So it's the second
or third slide.

01:09:38.710 --> 01:09:39.109
PROFESSOR: Yeah.

01:09:39.109 --> 01:09:39.990
That's right.

