01:09:52.790 --> 01:09:54.600
I want to know.

01:09:54.600 --> 01:09:55.860
That's a drawing in.

01:09:55.860 --> 01:09:57.100
And then you get to the
punchline, which

01:09:57.100 --> 01:09:58.210
is, yes, you can.

01:09:58.210 --> 01:10:01.410
And the goals are to see this
all over and see these three

01:10:01.410 --> 01:10:04.095
principles that we just used
and really understand them.

01:10:07.010 --> 01:10:11.470
OK Another one be bold,
so bold gestures.

01:10:17.350 --> 01:10:20.410
Bold gestures, voice,
you'll see that all

01:10:20.410 --> 01:10:21.660
throughout Walter Lewin.

01:10:24.160 --> 01:10:27.320
Another one, we've actually
done, I would say, a lot more

01:10:27.320 --> 01:10:30.082
with it than you saw in the
lecture, which is--

01:10:36.270 --> 01:10:40.000
And the third one is you want
to involve the audience by

01:10:40.000 --> 01:10:42.590
asking them questions, making
your whole lecture

01:10:42.590 --> 01:10:43.200
interactive.

01:10:43.200 --> 01:10:45.580
So we've discussed, actually,
many ways where the Lewin

01:10:45.580 --> 01:10:49.170
lecture could be improved
in that direction.

01:10:49.170 --> 01:10:53.030
And perhaps underlying
everything, none of this

01:10:53.030 --> 01:11:00.050
really works unless there's
principal four, which is that

01:11:00.050 --> 01:11:01.630
you have to care.

01:11:01.630 --> 01:11:03.660
You have to really, really love
what you're doing and

01:11:03.660 --> 01:11:05.660
transmit that to the students.

01:11:05.660 --> 01:11:08.730
And then, all of these
things become so much

01:11:08.730 --> 01:11:10.760
easier when you care.

01:11:10.760 --> 01:11:15.660
So those are the fundamental
principles of lecture

01:11:15.660 --> 01:11:17.510
performing and, basically,
planning

01:11:17.510 --> 01:11:18.980
around things like that.

01:11:18.980 --> 01:11:22.200
And if I just had written those
down in the beginning,

01:11:22.200 --> 01:11:23.340
it wouldn't have made sense.

01:11:23.340 --> 01:11:26.470
But now you've seen many, many,
many examples, and we've

01:11:26.470 --> 01:11:31.240
had many discussions about it
that I wish you success in

01:11:31.240 --> 01:11:35.180
applying good timing, good
bold gestures, strong

01:11:35.180 --> 01:11:39.290
gestures, and involving the
audience, not just emotionally

01:11:39.290 --> 01:11:44.490
or cognitively but both, so that
you provide long-lasting

01:11:44.490 --> 01:11:47.930
learning and interest in the
subject that you love.

01:11:47.930 --> 01:11:49.010
OK.

